<node id="Stock Markets">
  <data key="d0">Stock Markets</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Stock Markets are financial markets, systems, or venues primarily designed for the buying, selling, and trading of stocks or shares of publicly traded companies. These platforms are fundamental components of the global financial infrastructure, facilitating the exchange of equity within the overall financial system. Beyond stocks, Stock Markets also serve as venues for the trading of other securities.

As of today, Stock Markets are experiencing a sharp downturn, characterized by significant declines in stock values. This decline serves as a significant indicator of overall market performance, with notable decreases particularly among major technology companies. The downturn has been influenced by a combination of various economic factors and broader investor concerns that have impacted overall market sentiment.</data>
