<node id="Safe-Haven Assets">
  <data key="d0">Safe-Haven Assets</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Safe-Haven Assets are a distinct class of investments actively sought by investors during periods characterized by market uncertainty, downturns, turbulence, instability, volatility, or when other markets are experiencing a selloff or adverse conditions. These assets are primarily utilized as a protective measure against broader market declines, serving to safeguard and preserve capital. Investors turn to Safe-Haven Assets with the explicit goal of finding refuge from adverse market conditions.

A key distinguishing feature of Safe-Haven Assets is the expectation that they will either retain or increase in value during times of market turbulence, even as other investments may decline. This characteristic makes them a crucial tool for capital preservation when broader markets are under pressure.

Prominent examples of Safe-Haven Assets include gold and gold futures. Gold futures, in particular, are frequently observed to experience rising demand as investors actively seek them out during market downturns and periods of uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;Safe-haven assets are investments sought by investors during market uncertainty, such as gold.&lt;SEP&gt;Investors sought safe-haven assets, leading to a rise in gold futures.&lt;SEP&gt;Investors sought safe-haven assets like gold during the market downturn.&lt;SEP&gt;Investors sought safe-haven assets, leading to a rise in gold futures.&lt;SEP&gt;Safe-haven assets are investments sought by investors during market turbulence to preserve capital.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-68766b231992936270936e6f0b183e36&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2447fe875b384c188ba9d3554399dc6d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-532256487602de4be2e3c0e854913102&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b02689c99575169a9478479eec80788c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56282f4606fc56d4130b6951eb4c498d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f484700b8f584c97b2a965ce95f5d752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3b5730698c6919a72fa8fe9e365553a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bfb82ef2f9104c844470a7787413791&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58b3e6c838a45a3d906d10fc138ce489&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4a55c2cba84b3e6fcdc01243ddae25b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-077f1c8d65370143de742282e9519342&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53c122a1351bb62d4818744846fb8b3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-096f30b71c633363da29aedb33921bbe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ba233fdd570e49e5ca9f9ac3aab2be3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f54a987a86574adfb4ad1cb14029944a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-651844ca8fc582eb9e5c5ae952cda217&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9322d396cbf361d7f17eda716eeff69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc975fc447484d2d11d8799d6ecf1373&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf32d76f6af2b946cb3db4a54c84bdab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3586dcab6b282878bcaf595ac6fd2245&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2db7e0c2a92a184a27e188bc4286ed70&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5c6e8c62a21c8afb975734578cc2331&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ff117209416e691729376fe4458e772&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942fb16b5690c9bee8baf317da4683f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd5518f677237e7383fa30dabc5ab818&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b49052807e826628e673ce95e0a65779&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-013979dddee9fc5949155b21705bc9be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a021472a4b1810bb9115f956313f4eb2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbf7a61e9910d0b949699c42c00b1607&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5e29f86aac7deb2036ce96b4fbd5a21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-873a2f7c0b11e6a65564e71b9d136ab9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95087ad5658addfcfa23bfff3025dddc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6959a8e57f671bac210859bec155307</data>
