<node id="Supply Constraints">
  <data key="d0">Supply Constraints</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Supply Constraints are defined as limitations in the availability of goods, resources, or services. These limitations can specifically refer to the availability of commodities, such as crude oil.

As a significant economic factor, Supply Constraints are consistently noted for supporting the rally in crude oil prices. They contribute to the increase in crude oil valuations and are recognized as a key driver behind upward movements in market dynamics for this commodity. More generally, Supply Constraints contribute to rising prices across various commodity markets.&lt;SEP&gt;Limitations on the availability of goods, such as crude oil, contributing to price increases.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply constraints are limitations on the availability of goods, supporting crude oil price rallies.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply constraints supported the rally in crude oil prices.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply constraints supported the rally in crude oil prices.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply constraints are limitations on the availability of goods or resources.</data>
