<node id="Federal Reserve">
  <data key="d0">Federal Reserve</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Federal Reserve is the central banking system of the United States, serving as the nation's central bank. It is also characterized as a significant financial institution and an organization.

The actions, upcoming policy moves, and policy announcements of the Federal Reserve are intensely scrutinized and closely monitored by financial experts. This widespread attention is largely driven by speculation and anticipation concerning potential rate hikes. The Federal Reserve's decisions hold substantial influence over financial markets and overall market stability, with its policy announcements particularly known to influence market stability.</data>
