<node id="Rate Hikes">
  <data key="d0">Rate Hikes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">"Rate Hikes" refer to increases in interest rates, which are typically initiated by a central bank, most notably the Federal Reserve. These adjustments serve as a key monetary policy tool, primarily employed to control inflation or cool an overheating economy.

There is significant and growing speculation surrounding the Federal Reserve's potential actions concerning these interest rate increases. This widespread anticipation and discussion are a constant point of focus within financial markets, directly influencing investor confidence and playing a crucial role in determining overall market stability.&lt;SEP&gt;Increases in interest rates by a central bank, currently a subject of speculation regarding the Federal Reserve.&lt;SEP&gt;Rate hikes are increases in interest rates, with speculation growing over potential moves by the Federal Reserve.&lt;SEP&gt;Speculation grows over potential rate hikes by the Federal Reserve.&lt;SEP&gt;Rate hikes are increases in interest rates, often implemented by a central bank.</data>
