  <data key="d2">Gold futures are defined as financial contracts or instruments designed for the future delivery of gold. Recently, these financial instruments experienced a notable increase, rising by 1.5%. This upward movement in Gold futures is indicative of heightened investor interest in safe-haven assets, reflecting a market sentiment where investors are actively seeking such secure investments.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures are financial contracts that rose by 1.5%, indicating increased investor interest in safe-haven assets.</data>
