  <data key="d2">Crude oil is characterized as a natural resource, a commodity, and a raw material that is actively traded in markets.

Recently, crude oil prices have experienced a significant rally, climbing to $87.60 per barrel. This upward trend in prices is consistently attributed to a combination of market dynamics.

Specifically, the continued rally in crude oil prices is supported by prevailing supply constraints and robust demand for the resource. These factors have collectively driven the price increases to the noted level.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil is a natural resource whose prices rose to $87.60 per barrel due to supply constraints and strong demand.</data>
