  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) is a technique that utilizes external documents to generate answers, addressing LLM limitations like outdated information and hallucination.&lt;SEP&gt;A "retrieval-based generation" technique where Large Language Models (LLMs) utilize external documents for answer generation, addressing issues like LLM's lack of up-to-date information and hallucination.&lt;SEP&gt;A "search-based generation" technique that retrieves external documents to generate answers. It is necessary to address the issues of lack of up-to-date information and hallucination in LLMs.&lt;SEP&gt;A technique that enhances LLM answer generation by retrieving and utilizing external documents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AI Prompt Project">
  <data key="d0">AI Prompt Project</data>
  <data key="d1">project</data>
  <data key="d2">A project that utilizes RAG technology.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772696842</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vector DB">
  <data key="d0">Vector DB</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Vector DB is a database specialized for storing and performing high-speed searches on vector embeddings.&lt;SEP&gt;A database designed to store vector data and enable high-speed searching.&lt;SEP&gt;A database that stores vector data and enables high-speed searching. It is used in RAG systems to store document embeddings and search for similar documents.&lt;SEP&gt;A database designed to store and efficiently search vector embeddings, a key component of a RAG system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Milvus">
  <data key="d0">Milvus</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Milvus is a specific vector database known for high-speed vector search and indexing, used in RAG systems.&lt;SEP&gt;A vector database capable of high-speed vector search, scalability, GPU acceleration, and simultaneous management of vector and metadata.&lt;SEP&gt;A vector database capable of high-speed vector search, scalability, GPU acceleration, and concurrent management of vectors and metadata. It is utilized in building RAG systems.&lt;SEP&gt;A vector database tool utilized in RAG system construction, known for high-speed vector search, scalability, and GPU acceleration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LangChain">
  <data key="d0">LangChain</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">LangChain is an LLM framework used to construct the entire RAG chain, including document loading, vectorization, search, prompt configuration, and call connection.&lt;SEP&gt;A modular LLM framework for constructing RAG pipelines, including document loading, vectorization, search, prompt composition, and call connections. It can integrate with various tools like OpenAI, Cohere, Huggingface, and Milvus.&lt;SEP&gt;A framework for developing LLM applications, offering modular chain configuration, versatility, scalability, RAG-specific chains, and conversational QA support.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OpenAI ChatGPT (API)">
  <data key="d0">OpenAI ChatGPT (API)</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">OpenAI ChatGPT (API) is an LLM serving tool for natural language generation.&lt;SEP&gt;An LLM serving tool provided in API form.&lt;SEP&gt;An LLM serving service provided in API form. It can be used in RAG systems for generating answers based on search results and can be replaced by OpenLLMs like LLAMA in the future.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transformers">
  <data key="d0">Transformers</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Transformers is an LLM library used for local LLM execution, inference, and embedding generation.&lt;SEP&gt;An LLM library for running and inferring various LLMs locally and generating embeddings.&lt;SEP&gt;A library for loading and utilizing LLM models. It is used for local LLM execution, inference, and embedding generation.&lt;SEP&gt;A library used for working with Large Language Models and for generating embeddings.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LLAMA">
  <data key="d0">LLAMA</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">LLAMA is an OpenLLM that can be used as an alternative to OpenAI ChatGPT.&lt;SEP&gt;One of the OpenLLMs that can replace OpenAI ChatGPT (API).&lt;SEP&gt;An OpenLLM that can potentially replace OpenAI ChatGPT (API) in RAG systems.&lt;SEP&gt;A large language model that can serve as an alternative to OpenAI ChatGPT API.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OpenLLM">
  <data key="d0">OpenLLM</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">OpenLLM is a type of Large Language Model.&lt;SEP&gt;An open-source Large Language Model (LLM).&lt;SEP&gt;A category of open-source large language models that can serve as alternatives to proprietary LLM services like OpenAI ChatGPT (API).&lt;SEP&gt;An open-source large language model that can serve as an alternative to OpenAI ChatGPT API.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697213</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GPU Server">
  <data key="d0">GPU Server</data>
  <data key="d1">system</data>
  <data key="d2">A GPU Server is hardware required for optimizing LLM inference.&lt;SEP&gt;Hardware infrastructure for LLM inference and optimization.&lt;SEP&gt;A server equipped with Graphics Processing Units, necessary for LLM inference optimization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697217</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Document Searching">
  <data key="d0">Document Searching</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A function within the RAG system for searching external documents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772696842</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Embedding">
  <data key="d0">Embedding</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Embedding is the process of converting data into vector representations within the RAG pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;The process of converting query and document data into vectors.&lt;SEP&gt;The process or result of converting text data into numerical values in a vector space.&lt;SEP&gt;Numerical representations generated from text, used in RAG systems and created by tools like Transformers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Indexing">
  <data key="d0">Indexing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Indexing is a method to improve data retrieval efficiency, part of RAG testing and advancement.&lt;SEP&gt;The process of dividing documents into smaller parts and storing them appropriately to enhance data search efficiency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772696842</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Prompt Design">
  <data key="d0">Prompt Design</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The process of meticulously designing instructions (prompts) to improve the response quality of Large Language Models (LLMs).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772696842</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RAG Pipeline">
  <data key="d0">RAG Pipeline</data>
  <data key="d1">system</data>
  <data key="d2">The overall structure of a RAG system, encompassing query, indexing, search, and generation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772696842</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Halucination">
  <data key="d0">Halucination</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A phenomenon where Large Language Models (LLMs) generate false information about topics they do not know.&lt;SEP&gt;The phenomenon where an LLM generates information that is factually incorrect.&lt;SEP&gt;The problem of LLMs generating factually incorrect or nonsensical information, which RAG helps to mitigate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1772697212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Query Optimization">
  <data key="d0">Query Optimization</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Query Optimization is a method to improve the effectiveness of queries, part of RAG testing and advancement.&lt;SEP&gt;The process of modifying or manipulating the query process of RAG input to better express or handle user query intent.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a0547158026e43fb8dcad61fe81ede2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d141f18a9aab4498557bd2c9197355e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
