<edge source="Global Tech Index" target="Market Selloff">
  <data key="d7">22.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Global Tech Index, Market Selloff)" describes a scenario where a decline or drop observed in the Global Tech Index is an integral component of a wider market selloff. This movement in the Global Tech Index is indicative of the broader market downturn.

The broader market selloff, of which the Global Tech Index's decline is a part, is primarily attributed to and driven by prevailing investor concerns. Therefore, the drop in the Global Tech Index serves as a key indicator and reflection of this larger market trend, which is fundamentally influenced by these anxieties among investors.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.</data>
  <data key="d9">indicator,investor sentiment,market event,market performance,part of</data>
