<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Stock Markets">
  <data key="d7">47.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Market Selloff, Stock Markets)" describes a scenario where stock markets experience a significant and often rapid downturn. This event is consistently characterized, referred to, or described as a "market selloff," representing a substantial decrease in the overall value and performance of stock markets.

While such a downturn can occur on a specific day, indicating a recent event, the fundamental meaning of this relation encompasses any instance of a sharp and rapid decline in stock market value. The various descriptions consistently identify this phenomenon as a market selloff when stock markets face a sharp downturn.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock markets faced a sharp downturn today, characterized as a market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock markets faced a sharp downturn, referred to as a market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock markets experienced a sharp downturn, which is referred to as a market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock markets faced a sharp downturn today, leading to a market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock markets faced a sharp downturn, which is referred to as a market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Stock markets experienced a sharp downturn, referred to as a market selloff.</data>
