<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Analysts">
  <data key="d7">33.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation (Analysts, Market Selloff) describes the attribution made by financial analysts regarding the underlying causes of a market selloff. Financial analysts consistently identify investor concerns as the primary factor driving such market downturns.

These investor concerns are often characterized as various or specific, indicating that a multitude of different factors contribute to the apprehension among investors. This widespread apprehension ultimately leads to significant selling activity in the market, resulting in a market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Analysts attribute the market selloff to investor concerns.</data>
  <data key="d9">analysis,attributed cause,attributes cause,attribution,causal analysis,causal attribution,causation,cause</data>
