<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Gold Futures">
  <data key="d7">19.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between Gold Futures and a Market Selloff describes a financial dynamic where the value of gold, as traded through gold futures, tends to rise during periods of market instability. This upward movement in gold prices is primarily driven by investor behavior seeking to protect capital.

When a market selloff occurs, investors often seek to move their capital into assets perceived as less risky or more stable. Gold is traditionally considered a safe-haven asset, meaning it tends to retain or increase its value when other investments, such as stocks, are declining. Consequently, increased demand for gold during a market selloff leads to an appreciation in its price, which is reflected in the performance of gold futures.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold prices rose as investors sought safe-haven assets during the market selloff.</data>
  <data key="d9">market reaction,reaction to,safe-haven,safe-haven investment</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-0beb624e95d0a83ff827995041e5f87c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8de6e6c31fc329874fc387736b746d14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-532256487602de4be2e3c0e854913102&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bfb82ef2f9104c844470a7787413791&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3b5730698c6919a72fa8fe9e365553a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58b3e6c838a45a3d906d10fc138ce489&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-096f30b71c633363da29aedb33921bbe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4ad6777f6f372ddf6631e7703104954&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c6a355152f3149b1a67320fd1f08a52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f37adcf76bfa0b63b612de2654ab7ac6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9322d396cbf361d7f17eda716eeff69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d95555952d1fd191bad09dd2edf939dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3586dcab6b282878bcaf595ac6fd2245&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-189c87d63b8e6e2a4b59cfb0545528f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04d7b67eb1f5269cf901bd85a6fa243d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b3c51912cd727db72eefcfd4ca93f3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5c6e8c62a21c8afb975734578cc2331&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b49052807e826628e673ce95e0a65779&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-873a2f7c0b11e6a65564e71b9d136ab9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6959a8e57f671bac210859bec155307</data>
