<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Investor Concerns">
  <data key="d7">13.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between Investor Concerns and Market Selloff describes a causal link where investor concerns are consistently identified and attributed as the primary cause for a market selloff. This attribution is frequently made by analysts, who observe and report on the market dynamics. Across various analyses, the sentiment and anxieties of investors are directly connected to significant downturns in the market, indicating that when investors harbor concerns, these worries translate into actions that precipitate a market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;The market selloff is attributed to investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty are attributed as the cause of the market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Analysts attribute the market selloff to investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty are attributed as the cause for the market selloff.</data>
