<edge source="Investor Concerns" target="Rising Interest Rates">
  <data key="d7">16.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between Investor Concerns and Rising Interest Rates describes a scenario where apprehension among investors is directly and significantly linked to the phenomenon of increasing interest rates. Rising interest rates are identified as a central and specific factor contributing to these concerns, indicating a primary focus of investor worry.

This consistent observation across various contexts highlights that rising interest rates constitute a prominent source of worry for investors. These concerns directly influence investor decisions and overall market sentiment, driven by the potential implications and impacts associated with an environment of increasing interest rates. Consequently, rising interest rates are considered a key component of broader investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are related to rising interest rates.</data>
  <data key="d9">causal factor,causation,cause,component,concern,concern over,contributing factor,driven by,economic factor,economic influence,factor,focus,includes,market drivers,market factor,market sentiment,related to</data>
