<edge source="Investor Concerns" target="Regulatory Uncertainty">
  <data key="d7">18.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Investor Concerns, Regulatory Uncertainty)" describes a scenario where the presence of regulatory uncertainty is a primary focus or driver of investor concerns. This indicates that a lack of clarity, predictability, or stability within regulatory frameworks constitutes a significant factor influencing investor sentiment and decision-making.

Regulatory uncertainty serves as a key source and component of investor concerns. Investors are specifically troubled by the unknown or evolving nature of regulations, as this can directly impact their investments and overall market outlook. The unpredictable regulatory environment therefore plays a crucial role in shaping investor perceptions and actions.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are related to regulatory uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are over regulatory uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are related to regulatory uncertainty.</data>
