<edge source="1.5% Rise" target="Gold Futures">
  <data key="d7">26.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(1.5% Rise, Gold Futures)" describes a specific market movement characterized by an increase in the price of gold futures. This signifies that contracts for the future delivery of gold experienced an upward trend, with their market value appreciating by a margin of 1.5%. This rise reflects a positive change in the overall market valuation of gold futures.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures rose by 1.5%.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures rose by 1.5%.</data>
