<edge source="Investors" target="Safe-Haven Assets">
  <data key="d7">17.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Investors, Safe-Haven Assets)" describes a specific behavior observed among investors in financial markets. It indicates that investors actively seek out safe-haven assets as part of their investment strategy.

This behavior is predominantly triggered during periods of market uncertainty, economic turbulence, or heightened market volatility. Investors are motivated to pursue safe-haven assets due to the perception that these assets are likely to retain or even increase in value when broader markets are experiencing downturns or instability. A prominent example of such an asset frequently sought by investors is gold, including gold futures.</data>
  <data key="d9">asset seeking,investment strategy,market behavior,market reaction,preference,seeking,sought</data>
