<edge source="Safe-Haven Assets" target="Gold Futures">
  <data key="d7">25.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between Gold Futures and Safe-Haven Assets describes the established perception and market behavior where gold futures are consistently regarded by investors as safe-haven assets. This classification signifies that investors actively seek gold futures as a secure store of value, particularly during periods of market uncertainty or economic instability.

Consequently, when investors are seeking safe-haven assets, there is a notable tendency for the value of gold futures to rise. This dynamic reflects investors' inclination to turn to gold futures as a secure store of value, especially during times of market uncertainty or economic instability.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures are considered safe-haven assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures rose as investors sought safe-haven assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures are considered safe-haven assets by investors.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures are sought as safe-haven assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold futures are sought as safe-haven assets.</data>
