<edge source="$87.60 Per Barrel" target="Crude Oil">
  <data key="d7">17.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "($87.60 Per Barrel, Crude Oil)" describes a specific valuation point for crude oil. It indicates that the price of crude oil reached $87.60 per barrel, reflecting an upward movement in its market value. This figure represents a notable price level achieved by crude oil.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices climbed to $87.60 per barrel.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices climbed to $87.60 per barrel.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices climbed to $87.60 per barrel.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices climbed to $87.60 per barrel.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices climbed to $87.60 per barrel.</data>
