<edge source="Strong Demand" target="Crude Oil">
  <data key="d7">39.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Crude Oil, Strong Demand)" describes a fundamental market scenario where robust demand for crude oil acts as a significant factor influencing its market value. This relationship indicates a direct correlation, where increased consumption or a consistent need for crude oil consistently provides support for its prices.

Specifically, strong demand for crude oil is identified as a key element that contributes to maintaining or elevating crude oil price levels in the market. This consistent support from robust demand underscores its paramount importance in the overall dynamics of crude oil pricing. The consistent observation is that crude oil prices are, or have been, directly supported by strong demand.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.</data>
