<edge source="Financial Experts" target="Federal Reserve">
  <data key="d7">46.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between the Federal Reserve and financial experts is defined by intense scrutiny and close observation. Financial experts consistently and closely monitor the Federal Reserve's activities, with a primary focus on anticipating its future actions and policy decisions. This vigilance encompasses understanding the Federal Reserve's overall operations and, more specifically, its upcoming "next move" or "next moves." These anticipated actions refer to potential monetary policy adjustments, official statements, or other significant economic interventions that the Federal Reserve might undertake.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial experts are closely watching the Federal Reserve.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial experts are closely watching the Federal Reserve's next move.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial experts are closely watching the Federal Reserve's next move.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial experts are closely watching the Federal Reserve's next move.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial experts are closely watching the Federal Reserve.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial experts are closely watching the Federal Reserve's next move.</data>
